  "text": "The cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor p21 contributes to cell cycle arrest during the G0/G1 phase and cellular hypertrophy under various conditions and organs. [CITATION_1] [21] [CITATION_2] We found that p21 was remarkably upregulated at 24 h after 20 min of warm ischemia and 70% PH in PH. This suggests that the infusion of anti-HMGB1 mAb can prevent the signaling progression of hepatocyte hypertrophy and generate a shift to a state in which liver regeneration mainly depends on hepatocyte proliferation. STAT3 was rapidly phosphorylated and then recovered to the basal level within 24 h in the Hx group, but remained phosphorylated in the IRHxC group. The anti-HMGB1 mAb augmented STAT3 phosphorylation at 2 h and sustained it for up to 24 h after IRI and 70%",
